The Financial Action Task Force (FATF) updates its guidance on virtual asset service providers (VASPs), emphasizing the importance of effective AML/CFT measures in the crypto sector. Stay compliant to mitigate risks

The SEC clarifies its stance on decentralized finance (DeFi) platforms, signaling increased scrutiny and potential regulatory actions. DeFi projects should prioritize compliance and engage with regulators to ensure legitimacy

Regulatory Announcement: Japan's Financial Services Agency (FSA) introduces new licensing requirements for cryptocurrency custodians, aiming to strengthen consumer protection and safeguard assets. Compliance is non-negotiable.

The IRS updates its guidance on cryptocurrency taxation, providing clarity on reporting requirements and taxable events. Stay informed to fulfill your tax obligations and avoid penalties.

The SEC announces enforcement actions against unregistered cryptocurrency exchanges, emphasizing the importance of compliance with securities laws. Market participants should prioritize regulatory compliance to mitigate legal risks

The Financial Crimes Enforcement Network (FinCEN) proposes new rules for cryptocurrency transactions, including enhanced KYC/AML requirements and reporting obligations. Compliance is crucial for maintaining regulatory compliance

The European Central Bank (ECB) outlines its approach to central bank digital currencies (CBDCs), emphasizing regulatory considerations and potential risks. Market participants should monitor developments and assess regulatory implications.

The Australian Securities and Investments Commission (ASIC) issues guidance on initial coin offerings (ICOs), highlighting regulatory requirements and investor protection measures. Compliance is essential for ICO issuers and investors alike.

The Financial Stability Board (FSB) releases a report on stablecoins, addressing regulatory challenges and potential implications for financial stability. Stay informed to navigate the evolving regulatory landscape

The Monetary Authority of Singapore (MAS) announces new licensing requirements for cryptocurrency exchanges and payment service providers, aiming to enhance regulatory oversight and consumer protection. Compliance is paramount
